@146  = ~If it's like that, then goals are noble and just. In exchange for a donation of one thousand gold pieces, I'll remove the binding from the weapon.~
@147  = ~Wait a moment, I must ask <CHARNAME> for permission.~
@148  = ~*Ahem* <CHARNAME>, would you please give me one thousand gold pieces to be able to use Yoshimo's katana? Yo know how much I would love to use it, but, if you'd rather not do so, I won't insist too much.~
@149  = ~Pleasepleasepleaseplease!~
@150  = ~One thousand gold pieces for a blade that's only worth thirty? That's a no.~
@151  = ~I'd like to, but I don't have enough coin.~
@152  = ~I imagine that Yoshimo would be happy to know that his blade passed to you. Here's the money you need.~
@153  = ~I'll give you them, but on a condition: *don't* use it to hunt seagulls. Have I made myself clear?~
@154  = ~(Snort!) You're meaner than a flock of raging seagulls!~
@155  = ~Don't worry about it, I'll handle this! I'll empty all pockets in Athkatla, if needed!~
@156  = ~Hey, you! Don't move from here! We'll be back with the sum you asked, okay?~
@157  = ~Yeah! You're great, <CHARNAME>! I always said that you're a true friend! Thanks, thanks!~
@158  = ~Heh. As you wish. We're armed to the teeth, so I won't have trouble finding another weapon with which to gut those birds!~
@159  = ~Either way, thanks, <CHARNAME>. You're great! I always said you're unique!~
@160  = ~Should you change idea, <PRO_BROTHERSISTER>, you'll find me here. Meanwhile, I'll go back to easing other people's suffering in the name of the Crying God.~
@161  = ~I'll wait for you here. Meanwhile, I'll go back to easing other people's suffering in the name of the Crying God .~
@162  = ~The good soul and kind heart of Ilmater mean that He's not easy to anger, but he doesn't spare his wrath against those who caused great suffering. Might this blade avenge your friend's unjust sorrow.~
@163  = ~Here you go. You'll always be welcome in the house of the Crying God.~
@164  = ~YEAH! <CHARNAME>, I don't know how to thank you! Finally I can use it!!~
@165  = ~Ooohhhhooohhhaaah!~
@166  = ~Heh. This weapon holds incredible potential. I'm sure that the dwarf in the Docks we've already visited might improve on it. Either way, I'm euphoric!~
@167  = ~Heh. This weapon holds incredible potential. If I'm not mistaken, there's a dwarf in the Docks that might improve on it. Either way, I'm euphoric!~
